@egede I would argue to keep the functionality that this offers as a nice dictionary in the repo metadata to map jobs together. This could be very useful for systems such as Tasks etc in the near future to keep track of what jobs are being used for what.

That being said if this quickly amounts to a lot of work to keep something which is a nicety I'm all for dropping this.
If we dropped this then only the 'prep' registry has a need for a metadata registry attached to itself so I'd be for reducing this functionality to the special case of the prep registry.

