@ohemorange I think the questions of redirects on non-80 HTTP blocks, and of installing certs to non-443 TLS blocks, are largely orthogonal.

I'm pretty sure that installing the certs is mostly a good idea (though one day we may want a flag to control that behaviour.

I really don't know the best answer for redirects. I can see a case for: ship what we have, but open a wishlist ticket to implement a flag to control this in the future; change to be more conservative per @bmw's suggestion, with or without the future flag.  Probably I lean towards doing whatever will let us ship 0.9.0 for now :)

